San Francisco Police Chief Greg Suhr said he has recommended firing the eight officers . 
  The officers are accused of sending racist and homophobic texts between 2011 and 2012 . 
  The texts were sent to blacks, Mexicans, Filipinos and gay men . 
  The messages were uncovered after federal corruption charges were brought against a former sergeant . 
  The eight officers have been suspended and Suhr has recommended they be fired . 
  Michael Robison, 46, a 23-year veteran of the force, has resigned . 
  Six others will face disciplinary action . 
  The offensive texts were discovered by federal authorities investigating former sergeant Ian Furminger . 
 